body:
I suppose this might be the culprit:

    func (c *folderSummaryService) listenForUpdates(ctx context.Context) error {
	    sub := c.evLogger.Subscribe(events.LocalIndexUpdated | events.RemoteIndexUpdated | events.StateChanged | events.RemoteDownloadProgress | events.DeviceConnected | events.FolderWatchStateChanged | events.DownloadProgress)

There is simply no event that triggers this again after receiving a new ClusterConfig from the remote with the folder now included.  Thus the completion is not recalculated and the state won't change in the GUI.  Refreshing will pull the completion for all folders from the endpoint again, thus fixing the display "manually".

@imsodin does that sound like a sensible explanation?  I guess updating completion when the remote ClusterConfig changes would be a good idea anyway.  But maybe I just don't see where it's already done.
